-- S&P 500 hits lifetime record, surpasses 2000 high
-- 
-- Fri Jul 13, 2007 2:50pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/13/us-markets-stocks-sp-idUSN1339248620070713

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The S&P 500 index, a measure of the largest U.S. stocks, rose to a lifetime high on Friday on optimism about economic growth, corporate takeovers and profits. 

 The previous record of 1,553.11 was set on March 24, 2000. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index  .SPX  was up 5.99 points, or 0.39 percent, at 1,553.69. The Dow Jones industrial average  .DJI  was up 49.99 points, or 0.36 percent, at 13,911.72. The Nasdaq Composite Index  .IXIC  was up 1.37 points, or 0.05 percent, at 2,703.10.